<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-60-0945 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper presents the prospects for renewable energy use in Canada.The 1978 market is examined followed by a discussion of nine renewableoptions: solar space and water heating, hard solar, forecast biomasss,agricultural biomass, wind, tidal power, ocean thermal gradients, goethermalenergy, and the traditional hydroelectricity. There is a short discusssionof the roles for government in encouraging renewable development. 35refs., 3 figs., 2 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>